<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>wise as a Christian • wise as Solomon</xh5><p> <i>wise as a Christian</i>—(of an animal) intelligent: Then he rubbed Feenish, the mare, all over, and instantly she became as <u>wise as a Christian</u>, and knew every word that was said to her.</p><p> <i>wise as Solomon—</i>having good judgment; very shrewd: In some of the divorce cases one would need to be as <u>wise as Solomon</u> to know which party was the more at fault.</p> </entry>
